==Old English==
===Etymology===
From a Germanic base corresponding to the roots of [[for-#Old English|for-]] + [[etan]].  Cognate with Old Saxon ''fretan'' (Dutch [[vreten]]), Old High German [[frezzan]] (German [[fressen]]), Gothic [[𐍆𐍂𐌰𐌹𐍄𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'fretan/}}

===Verb===
'''fretan''' (class V strong)
# to [[devour]], [[consume]]

